.\" Man page for proj
.\" To install: sudo mkdir -p /usr/local/share/man/man1 && sudo cp man/proj.1 /usr/local/share/man/man1/ && sudo mandb
.\" To view: man proj
.\"
.TH PROJ 1 "2026-03-01" "proj 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
proj \- manage all your projects from the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B proj
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B proj
is a fast CLI for managing all your projects across local directories and GitHub. It provides instant project switching via fuzzy search, unified sync status tracking, quality checks, and seamless GitHub integration.
.PP
Key capabilities:
.IP \(bu 2
Instant fuzzy search navigation across all projects
.IP \(bu 2
Unified dashboard showing local and remote repositories
.IP \(bu 2
Smart sync tracking (dirty, ahead, behind, diverged)
.IP \(bu 2
AI-powered code quality checks
.IP \(bu 2
GitHub integration (clone, create, browse)
.IP \(bu 2
Shell integration for instant directory changes
.IP \(bu 2
Rich metadata (language, stars, last push time, dirty files)
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list, ls
List all projects (local + remote)
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-local
Show only local projects
.TP
.B \-\-remote
Show remote-only projects (on GitHub but not cloned)
.TP
.B \-\-all
Show all projects (default)
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj ls
proj ls --local
proj ls --remote
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B cd \fI[QUERY]\fR
Print path to project for shell wrapper (uses fuzzy search)
.RS
.TP
.I QUERY
Project name or fuzzy query. If omitted, shows an interactive picker.
.PP
Note: This command outputs a path. The shell wrapper function (see
.B SHELL INTEGRATION
below) captures this and performs the actual directory change.
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj cd faceswap-api
proj cd face           # Fuzzy matches faceswap-api
proj cd                # Interactive picker
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B clone \fINAME\fR
Clone a GitHub repository to projects directory
.RS
.TP
.I NAME
Repository name (supports fuzzy matching against your GitHub repos)
.PP
The repository is cloned to
.IR $projects_dir/<name> .
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj clone solidkit
proj clone solid       # Fuzzy matches solidkit
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B new \fINAME\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Create new project (directory + git + GitHub repo)
.RS
.TP
.I NAME
Project name (required)
.TP
.B \-\-public
Create public GitHub repository (default: private)
.TP
.B \-\-lang \fILANGUAGE\fR
Language for scaffolding. Supported: rust, js, py, go
.PP
Creates:
.IP \(bu 2
Local directory in
.I $projects_dir/<name>
.IP \(bu 2
Git repository (with initial commit)
.IP \(bu 2
GitHub repository (private by default)
.IP \(bu 2
Language-specific scaffolding (if --lang specified)
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj new my-app
proj new my-rust-crate --lang rust
proj new open-source-tool --public --lang js
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B sync
Show sync status dashboard
.RS
Displays:
.IP \(bu 2
Projects with unpushed commits (ahead)
.IP \(bu 2
Projects with uncommitted changes (dirty)
.IP \(bu 2
Projects without git tracking
.IP \(bu 2
Clean projects (synced)
.PP
.B Example:
.RS 2
.nf
proj sync
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B open \fINAME\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Open project in editor, browser, or file manager
.RS
.TP
.I NAME
Project name (supports fuzzy matching)
.TP
.B \-\-github
Open GitHub repository URL in browser
.TP
.B \-\-dir
Open project directory in file manager
.PP
Default behavior (no flags): Opens project in your configured editor (via
.B $EDITOR
environment variable or config file).
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj open solidkit                # Opens in editor
proj open solidkit --github       # Opens GitHub page
proj open solidkit --dir          # Opens in file manager
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B check \fINAME\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Run AI-powered code quality checks
.RS
.TP
.I NAME
Project name (supports fuzzy matching)
.TP
.B \-\-all
Run all available checks
.TP
.B \-\-check \fICHECK_TYPE\fR
Run specific check. Available types:
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
.B quality
\- Code quality, complexity, patterns
.IP \(bu 2
.B logging
\- Logging consistency, levels, structured logging
.IP \(bu 2
.B testing
\- Test coverage, test quality, missing tests
.IP \(bu 2
.B security
\- OWASP checks, dependency audit, secrets scan
.IP \(bu 2
.B docs
\- Documentation completeness, API docs
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-ai
Use AI (Claude CLI) for deeper analysis
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj check solidkit --all
proj check faceswap-api --check security
proj check my-app --check quality --ai
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B info \fINAME\fR
Show detailed project information
.RS
.TP
.I NAME
Project name (supports fuzzy matching)
.PP
Displays:
.IP \(bu 2
Local path
.IP \(bu 2
GitHub repository details (description, stars, language)
.IP \(bu 2
Git status (branch, dirty files, last commit)
.IP \(bu 2
Sync status (ahead, behind, diverged)
.IP \(bu 2
Last push time
.PP
.B Example:
.RS 2
.nf
proj info solidkit
.fi
.RE
.RE
.TP
.B init \fISHELL\fR
Output shell wrapper function for cd command
.RS
.TP
.I SHELL
Shell type: bash, zsh, or fish
.PP
Generates a shell function that wraps
.B proj cd
to enable directory changes in the parent shell. See
.B SHELL INTEGRATION
below for details.
.PP
.B Examples:
.RS 2
.nf
proj init bash
proj init zsh
proj init fish

# Typical usage (add to ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc):
eval "$(proj init bash)"
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B proj
reads configuration from
.IR ~/.config/proj/config.toml .
.PP
Example configuration:
.RS 4
.nf
# Directory containing local projects
projects_dir = "~/Projects"

# GitHub username for repository listing
github_username = "yourusername"

# Patterns to exclude from project discovery
exclude_patterns = [
    "node_modules",
    "target",
    ".git",
    "vendor"
]

# Custom quality checks
[checks]
rust = ["cargo clippy", "cargo test"]
typescript = ["npm run lint", "npm test"]
python = ["ruff check", "pytest"]
.fi
.RE
.PP
All fields are optional. Defaults:
.IP \(bu 2
.B projects_dir
\- ~/Projects
.IP \(bu 2
.B github_username
\- Detected from git config
.IP \(bu 2
.B exclude_patterns
\- node_modules, target, .git
.SH SHELL INTEGRATION
.B proj cd
cannot change the parent shell's directory directly. Instead, it outputs the target path and relies on a shell wrapper function to perform the actual directory change.
.PP
.B Setup (automatic):
.RS 4
.nf
# Add to ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc
eval "$(proj init bash)"   # or: zsh, fish
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Setup (manual):
.PP
If automatic setup doesn't work, add this function to
.I ~/.bashrc
or
.IR ~/.zshrc :
.RS 4
.nf
proj() {
    if [ "$1" = "cd" ]; then
        local result=$(command proj cd "$2")
        if [ -d "$result" ]; then
            cd "$result"
        else
            echo "$result"
        fi
    else
        command proj "$@"
    fi
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
For Fish shell, add to
.IR ~/.config/fish/config.fish :
.RS 4
.nf
function proj
    if test "$argv[1]" = "cd"
        set -l dir (command proj cd $argv[2])
        if test -d "$dir"
            cd "$dir"
        else
            echo "$dir"
        end
    else
        command proj $argv
    end
end
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B How it works:
.IP 1. 3
User runs
.B proj cd <query>
.IP 2. 3
Shell wrapper intercepts the command
.IP 3. 3
Wrapper calls
.B command proj cd <query>
to get the path
.IP 4. 3
Wrapper uses built-in
.B cd
to change directory
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
Default editor for
.BR "proj open" .
If not set, falls back to config file or
.BR vi .
.TP
.B GITHUB_TOKEN
GitHub personal access token. If not set,
.B proj
uses
.B gh
CLI's authentication (recommended).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/proj/config.toml
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/Projects/
Default projects directory (configurable)
.TP
.I ~/.bashrc, ~/.zshrc
Shell initialization files where
.B proj init
output should be added
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS List all local projects
.RS 4
.nf
proj ls --local
.fi
.RE
.SS Jump to a project using fuzzy search
.RS 4
.nf
proj cd face              # Matches 'faceswap-api'
proj cd solid             # Matches 'solidkit'
proj cd                   # Interactive picker
.fi
.RE
.SS Clone a repository from GitHub
.RS 4
.nf
proj clone my-repo
proj clone my-org/my-repo
.fi
.RE
.SS Create a new Rust project
.RS 4
.nf
proj new my-crate --lang rust
.fi
.RE
.SS Create a public JavaScript project
.RS 4
.nf
proj new open-source-lib --lang js --public
.fi
.RE
.SS Check which projects need attention
.RS 4
.nf
proj sync
.fi
.RE
.SS Open a project in your editor
.RS 4
.nf
proj open faceswap-api
.fi
.RE
.SS Open a project's GitHub page
.RS 4
.nf
proj open solidkit --github
.fi
.RE
.SS Run security checks on a project
.RS 4
.nf
proj check my-app --check security
.fi
.RE
.SS Run all quality checks with AI analysis
.RS 4
.nf
proj check my-app --all --ai
.fi
.RE
.SS View detailed project information
.RS 4
.nf
proj info solidkit
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, project not found, git/GitHub operation failed)
